==English==
{{swp}}

===Etymology===
{{bor+|en|de|Akronym}}, from {{der|en|grc|ἄκρον||[[end]], [[peak]]}} and {{m|grc|ὄνυμα||[[name]]}}, equivalent to {{af|en|acro-|-onym|t1=[[high]]; [[beginning]]|t2=[[name]]}}.<ref name=oed/> Modelled after {{m|de|Homonym}} and {{m|de|Synonym}}, first attested in German in the early 1900s<ref>Gerhard Stilz, ''Studien zur englischen Philologie, Nummer 21'', Niemeyer., 1905</ref> and in English in 1940.<ref name=oed>[http://www.oed.com/view/Entry/1844 "acronym, ''n.''"], in the ''Oxford English Dictionary'', Oxford: Oxford University Press.</ref>
{{root|en|ine-pro|*h₂eḱ-}}

